# Static HTML

- Use `<!DOCTYPE html>`, `<html lang="en">`, and `<meta charset="utf-8">` plus `<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">` on every page.
- Include a unique `<title>` and a useful `<meta name="description">`.
- One `<h1>` per page. Use `<header>`, `<main>`, `<footer>`, and `<section>` with stable `id` attributes for in-page anchors (`#meet-mac`, `#gallery`, etc.).
- Link CSS with `<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/...">` and JS with `<script src="js/..." defer></script>` relative to the HTML file.
- Provide a **skip link** to `#main` for keyboard users. All non-decorative images need meaningful `alt`; decorative images use `alt=""`.
- Avoid inline `style` except rare one-off cases; prefer **compiled Tailwind output** under `dist/css/` (filename per project, e.g. `styles.css`) and theme tokens—not ad hoc hex in attributes.

```html
<!-- Good: relative assets from dist/index.html (CSS = Tailwind build output) -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/main.css" />
<script src="js/main.js" defer></script>
```
